verbose_text: In our previous study, we demonstrated that succinate levels were elevated in the retinas of diabetic rats and that the knockdown of the succinate receptor, G-protein-coupled receptor 91 (GPR91), inhibited the release of VEGF and attenuated retinal vascular disorder in the early stages of DR.
evidence: G-protein-coupled receptor 91 (GPR91), inhibited the release of VEGF
